Subject: [ MDKSA-2006:104 ] - Updated sendmail packages fix remotely exploitable vulnerability



-----BEGIN PGP SIGNED MESSAGE-----
Hash: SHA1

 _______________________________________________________________________
 
 Mandriva Linux Security Advisory                         MDKSA-2006:104
 http://www.mandriva.com/security/
 _______________________________________________________________________
 
 Package : sendmail
 Date    : June 14, 2006
 Affected: 10.2, 2006.0, Corporate 3.0, Multi Network Firewall 2.0
 _______________________________________________________________________
 
 Problem Description:
 
 A vulnerability in the way Sendmail handles multi-part MIME messages
 was discovered that could allow a remote attacker to create a carefully
 crafted message that could crash the sendmail process during delivery.
 
 The updated packages have been patched to correct these issues.
 _______________________________________________________________________

 References:
 
 http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2006-1173
 http://www.cert.org/advisories/146718
 _______________________________________________________________________
 
